# FTQC Book Project

## What This Is
A Typst-based book on Fault-Tolerant Quantum Computation using Shiroa for static site generation. Auto-deployed to GitHub Pages at http://itpyi.site/spqr-ftqc/

## Project Structure
- `*.typ` - Book content files (Typst format)
- `book.typ` - Main book configuration with chapter structure
- `templates/` - Page templates and theme styling
- `dist/` - Generated output (gitignored, auto-built by CI)
- `.github/workflows/deploy.yml` - Auto-deployment to GitHub Pages

## Key Technical Details
- **Shiroa CLI**: v0.3.0 (matches local dev environment)
- **Shiroa Library**: @preview/shiroa:0.2.0 (in book.typ)
- **Build Command**: `shiroa build --path-to-root /spqr-ftqc/` (REQUIRED for correct paths)
- **Local Dev**: Use `./watch-and-serve.sh` for live reload

## DO
- Commit after each logical unit of work (e.g., per chapter update, per bug fix)
- Test locally with `./watch-and-serve.sh` before pushing
- Keep commits focused and atomic
- Update README/GUIDE.md if adding features or changing workflows

## DON'T
- Change shiroa versions without testing thoroughly (CLI/library must match)
- Remove `--path-to-root /spqr-ftqc/` from deploy.yml (breaks GitHub Pages)
- Commit the `dist/` directory (CI builds it)
- Change base paths without understanding implications

## Common Tasks
- **Add chapter**: Create `new-chapter.typ`, add to `book.typ` summary
- **Update content**: Edit `.typ` files, test locally, commit with descriptive message
- **Fix styling**: Modify `templates/page.typ` or `templates/theme-style.toml`
- **Deploy**: Just push to main branch - CI handles the rest

## Troubleshooting
- CSS not loading? Check `--path-to-root` in deploy.yml
- Build fails? Verify shiroa version compatibility
- Local preview? Use `./watch-and-serve.sh`, not `shiroa serve` alone
